*danh từ
 ■cây rau mùi

Anh - Anh
coriander
[ˌkɒrɪ'andə]
■ noun an aromatic Mediterranean plant of the parsley family, the leaves and seeds of which are used as culinary herbs. [Coriandrum sativum.]
Origin
ME: from OFr. coriandre, from L. coriandrum, from Gk koriannon.
